I got a brother in that land...

41:36.200 --> 41:40.600
I got a brother in that land...

41:40.800 --> 41:45.400
I got a brother in that land...

41:45.400 --> 41:48.500
Where I'm bound...

41:57.400 --> 41:59.500
So, uh...

41:59.500 --> 42:03.300
I get this message marked "urgent"...

42:03.300 --> 42:08.700
...on my answering service from one Fox Mantle
telling me to come down to the park...

42:08.700 --> 42:14.600
...for a very special very early or
very late birthday present.

42:14.600 --> 42:16.600
And, Mulder...

42:16.600 --> 42:21.100
I don't see any nicely wrapped
presents lying around so, what gives?

42:21.300 --> 42:25.600
- You've never hit a baseball, have you, Scully?
- No, I guess I have, uh...

42:25.600 --> 42:30.100
...found more necessary things
to do with my time than...

42:30.100 --> 42:33.600
...slap a piece of horsehide with a stick.

42:34.300 --> 42:37.100
Get over here, Scully.

42:46.700 --> 42:49.700
This my birthday present, Mulder?

42:49.900 --> 42:52.300
- You shouldn't have.
- This ain't cheap.

42:52.300 --> 42:56.400
I'm paying that kid ten bucks
an hour to shag balls.

42:57.400 --> 43:00.500
Hey, it's not a bad piece of ash, huh?

43:00.500 --> 43:05.600
The bat... talking about the bat. Now, don't
strangle it. You just want to shake hands with it.

43:05.600 --> 43:07.900
"Hello, Mr. Bat. It's a pleasure
to make your acquaintance."

43:07.900 --> 43:11.400
"Oh, no, no, Ms. Scully.
The pleasure's all mine."

43:11.400 --> 43:15.200
Okay, now, we want to... we want
to go hips before hands, okay?

43:15.200 --> 43:20.300
We want to stride forward and turn. That's all
we're thinking about. So, we go hips...

43:20.300 --> 43:22.100
- ...before hands, all right?
- Okay.

43:22.100 --> 43:23.400
One more time.

43:23.400 --> 43:26.400
- Hips... before hands, all right?
- Yeah.

43:26.400 --> 43:28.600
- What is it?
- Hips before hands.

43:28.600 --> 43:31.200
Right. We're going to wait on the pitch.
We're going to keep our eye on the ball.

43:31.200 --> 43:34.000
Then, we're just going to make contact.
We're not going to think.

43:34.000 --> 43:36.600
We're just going to let it fly, Scully, okay?

43:38.400 --> 43:40.800
- Ready?
- I'm in the middle.

43:42.700 --> 43:45.400
All right, fire away, Poorboy.

43:46.500 --> 43:47.800
That's good.

43:47.800 --> 43:52.300
All right, what you may find is you
concentrate on hitting that little ball...

43:52.300 --> 43:56.200
The rest of the world just fades away,
all your everyday, nagging concerns.

43:56.200 --> 43:58.400
The ticking of your biological clock.

43:58.400 --> 44:03.000
How you probably couldn't afford that nice,
new suede coat on a G-Woman's salary.

44:03.000 --> 44:06.000
How you threw away a promising
career in medicine...

44:06.000 --> 44:10.300
...to hunt aliens with a crackpot,
albeit brilliant, partner.

44:10.300 --> 44:14.200
Getting into the heart of a
global conspiracy.

44:14.200 --> 44:17.200
Your obscenely overdue triple-X bill.

44:17.200 --> 44:21.400
Oh, I... I'm sorry, Scully. Those last
two problems are mine, not yours.

44:21.400 --> 44:26.100
Shut up, Mulder.
I'm playing baseball.

